                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Griscom</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-12-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 18, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Griscom, referring to his dispatch of September 21, reports that the
                    Japanese minister for foreign affairs has informed him that the Russian reply
                    has been received, and that it is most unsatisfactory, that it treats solely of
                    Korea and ignores Manchuria, and that the Japanese Government will request
                    Russia to reconsider.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
